text: Zelmar Casco (31 July 1926 - 5 September 2020) was an Argentine fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1964 Summer Olympics. He was born in La Plata, Argentina. Casco died on 5 September 2020 in Buenos Aires at the age of 94. ==References== Category:1926 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Argentina Category:Argentine fencers
